				<td colspan="2"><span>1) You need three Warriors with Earthshakers.
<br />

<br />
2) All three Warriors are going to die.  Not &quot;extremely high chance,&quot; not &quot;maybe one will live&quot; - all three are going to die, guaranteed.
<br />

<br />
3) You need help from other classes.  The proc rate simply isn't high enough unless you get a Shaman to slow each Warrior beforehand, plus every time you're going to need a rez and buffs again.
<br />

<br />
4) Most of the experience goes to the third Warrior.
<br />

<br />
5) If you want to do it again, you have to wait for <i>all</i> the mobs to repop.  The trick doesn't work if you don't start out with enough mobs - pretty much every mob in the first field in Fire has to be up.
<br />

<br />
The Earthshaker &quot;exploit&quot; you're ranting about is a cute trick, and it makes for some great screenshots - but I'll bet you haven't seen it done more than once or twice.  It simply isn't an efficient method of gaining experience.  It certainly isn't solo experience.</span></td>
