			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: So where is the Earthshaker nerf?<a name="61555"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 12 04 6:36 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The problem with AE wasn't that a single bard could kite 100+ Nadox mobs, it's that any bard with a TDoK could go from 20s-65 + AAs extremely fast with small, managable AE kites. AEing 15-20 mobs at a time is already much much better exp that a group or any other form of soloing can get a player. </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
1. Bards AE with Lute/Horn ... not a drum.  Or do you mean the autocircle lot? If so, their dps would be much lower anyway and there would be limited mobs/locations for them to xp.
<br />

<br />
2. AE kiting 10 mobs (your<i> 'small and managable'</i>?) is identical to AE kiting 50 mobs from a bard's perspective (assuming fast connection).  Only thing increased is pull time.
<br />

<br />
3. Doing AE on <i>'15-20 mobs at a time'  </i> is NOT <i>'much much better exp' </i> than is possible elsewhere.  There have been lots of posts on this already.  If going '<i>20-65</i>' (including PL) is the goal, then its certainly not true 46+ (possible access to higher planes and sympathetic guild groups - tho to be fair even guild might not let one help in EP groups before 65).  Equally its not true upto about lvl 40 (recently leveled a mage 1 - 40 in about 8 hours using their mini-AE whilst zillions of mobs whacked my maxed DS -- a bard could be PL'd in the same way using an AE dot, and indeed the nerf as planned won't affect it).  
<br />

<br />
Do think before posting replies<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
