			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: So where is the Earthshaker nerf?<a name="61725"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 14 04 2:18 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1. Autocircle is the main source of the problem. Like I said, more or less any brainless fool can start a bard alt and rush to 65+AA with ease. If you read my post, the problem isn't the .05% of bards that can make huge exp kiting absurd amounts of mobs, it's the relatively high percentage of bards that can autocircle. Earthshaker abuse is very small and specialized, autocircle was way too common. 
<br />

<br />
2. Vastly increased likelihood of death. Getting caught once in a while is more or less inevitable, due to random warping and crap. 
<br />

<br />
3. Uh, 95% of EQ's population does not have access to EPs and guild groups/high level mains to PL themselves. However, many/most of them can scrape up 10k for some instruments. SOE is not aiming this nerf at the 65 EP+ crowd, it's the average (casual) gamers that are able to get several levels a night without enough risk to create doubt. Just by autocircling places like Dulak. Few people care if you can make 5 AA/hour solo and only 4 AA/hour in an EP group, because only a minority have so much as glimpsed PoFire. While most 65s are doing LDoNs and tier 2/3, and 65 unguilded bard can make exp faster and with alot less hassle than grouping. 
<br />

<br />
Maybe you would care to come out of the EPs once in a while and realize that most people are 'stuck' in a completely different game, and that it is SOEs focus to keep these people around? Everyone else is sick of a single bard holding down half of Dulak, they may not even have heard of an Earthshaker. So think about others before you post. You lost your AE, yeah, it hurts. Does this mean you need to cry nerf on every other unbalanced ability in the game? Frankly, bards should not be upset they lost the ability to AE kite, it was too powerful. Just be unhappy the songs now suck for all other purposes too.  
<br />

<br />
All this said, I don't care whether or not they nerf Earthshaker. I'm generally disinclined to support nerfs overall, but nerfing the Earthshaker will in no way damage warriors or anything else than removing this arguably too-powerful ability. 
<br />
